┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                                RunHaven Guide                                │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
┌ First Run ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│Start with the smallest workspace the agent needs. RunHaven mounts that one   │
│directory at /workspace.                                                      │
│                                                                              │
│Pick an agent, then review the plan before launch. The plan shows the         │
│workspace, state volume, network mode, egress posture, and equivalent CLI     │
│command.                                                                      │
│                                                                              │
│Secure-default plans launch with enter. Lower-security choices require        │
│typing run.                                                                   │
│                                                                              │
│Use d for the active-run dashboard, h for completed run history and diffs,    │
│and g for diagnostics. The CLI remains available for scripts, pipes,          │
│recovery, and worktree merge/discard.                                         │
│                                                                              │
│Accessibility controls: NO_COLOR disables color,                              │
│RUNHAVEN_TUI_REDUCED_MOTION=1 keeps motion static, RUNHAVEN_TUI_LINE_MODE=1   │
│uses a text-first layout, and RUNHAVEN_TUI_COLOR_MODE=light or dark selects   │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
   w workspace | r review | d dashboard | h history | g diagnostics | esc home
               Every TUI action maps back to a named CLI command.
